<text>
The uses-configuration section in the manifest allows you to specify required input methods for your device. For example, the following snippet would require that the device has a hardware keyboard.

<i><uses-configuration android:reqHardKeyboard="true"/></i>
The uses-feature section allows you to specify the required hardware configuration for your device.
<b>For example,</b> the following snippet would require that the device has a camera.

<i><uses-feature android:name="android.hardware.camera" /></i>
</text>